
*******************************Day 2: Temporary User Setup with Expiry***************************

As part of the temporary assignment to the Nautilus project, a developer named james requires access for a limited duration. To ensure smooth access management, a temporary user account with an expiry date is needed.  

Create a user named james on App Server 2 in Stratos Datacenter. Set the expiry date to 2024-04-15, ensuring the user is created in lowercase as per standard protocol.
-------------------
ANS :  

sudo adduser --expiredate 2023-12-07 stark 
sudo chage -l stark



[root@stapp01 ~]# groupadd nautilus_admin_users

[root@stapp01 ~]# id stark
id: ‘stark’: no such user

[root@stapp01 ~]# cat /etc/passwd | grep stark

[root@stapp01 ~]# useradd -G nautilus_admin_users  stark

[root@stapp01 ~]# id stark
uid=1002(stark) gid=1003(stark) groups=1003(stark),1002(nautilus_admin_users)

[root@stapp01 ~]# cat /etc/passwd |grep stark
stark:x:1002:1003::/home/stark:/bin/bash

[root@stapp01 ~]#


[sudo] password for steve: 
